'''Takeminawake no Mikoto''' (武美名別命) is an ancient figure of Japanese mythology.
== Overview == Takeminawake no Mikoto is considered to be the same deity as '''Takemizuwake Ōkami''' (武水別大神), the enshrined deity of [[Takemizuwake Shrine]], a [[Shikinaisha|ritual shrine]] listed in volumes 9 and 10 of the ''[[Engishiki]]'' under the [[Tōsandō]] [[Shinano Province]] [[Sarashina District]].
== Shrines Dedicated to Takeminawake == * [[Takemizuwake Shrine]] (八幡, [[Chikuma]], [[Nagano Prefecture]]) * [[Hichi Shrine]] ([[Ōoka]], [[Nagano]], Nagano Prefecture)
