'''Takeminawake no Mikoto''' (武美名別命) is a figure from ancient Japan.
== Overview == Takeminawake no Mikoto is considered the same deity as '''Takemizuwake Ōkami''' (武水別大神), worshipped at {{ill|Takemizuwake Shrine|ja|武水別神社}}, a {{ill|Shikinai-sha|ja|式内社}} mentioned in Volumes 9 and 10 of the {{ill|Engishiki|ja|延喜式}}. This shrine is located in the former {{ill|Sarashina District|ja|更級郡}}, {{ill|Shinano Province|ja|信濃国}}.
== Shrines == * {{ill|Takemizuwake Shrine|ja|武水別神社}} ({{ill|Chikuma, Nagano|ja|千曲市}}, Nagano Prefecture) * {{ill|Hijiri Shrine|ja|樋知大神社}} ({{ill|Nagano, Nagano|ja|長野市}}, Nagano Prefecture)
