{{Infobox Noble | name = Takeminawake no Mikoto | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | era = [[Ancient Japan]], [[Yayoi period]] | birth_date = Unknown | death_date = Unknown | other_names = Takemizuwake Ōkami, Takemizuwake no Mikoto, Hikowake no Mikoto, {{ill|Take-minakata-no-Hiko-Kamiwake-no-Mikoto|ja|建御名方彦神別命|1=Takeminakata Hikokamiwake no Mikoto|12=draft}} | posthumous_name = | divine_name = | Buddhist_name = | burial_place = | rank = | allegiance = | clan = | notable_achievements = [[Junior Second Rank]]; Deity worshipped at {{ill|Takemizuwake Shrine|ja|武水別神社|12=draft}} and {{ill|Hijiri Shrine|ja|樋知大神社|12=draft}}. }}
'''Takeminawake no Mikoto''' (武美名別命) is a figure from ancient Japan.
== Overview == Takeminawake no Mikoto is considered the same deity as '''Takemizuwake Ōkami''' (武水別大神), worshipped at {{ill|Takemizuwake Shrine|ja|武水別神社|12=draft}}, a {{ill|Shikinai-sha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|12=draft}} mentioned in Volumes 9 and 10 of the {{ill|Engishiki|ja|延喜式|12=draft}}. This shrine is located in the former {{ill|Sarashina District, Nagano|lt=Sarashina District|ja|更級郡|12=draft}}, {{ill|Shinano Province|ja|信濃国|12=draft}}.
== Shrines == * {{ill|Takemizuwake Shrine|ja|武水別神社|12=draft}} ({{ill|Chikuma, Nagano|ja|千曲市|12=draft}}, Nagano Prefecture) * {{ill|Hijiri Shrine|ja|樋知大神社|12=draft}} ({{ill|Nagano, Nagano|ja|長野市|12=draft}}, Nagano Prefecture)
