'''Takeminawake no Mikoto''' (武美名別命) is a figure from ancient Japan.
== Overview == Takeminawake no Mikoto is considered the same deity as '''Takemizuwake Ōkami''' (武水別大神), worshipped at {{ill|Takemizuwake Shrine|ja|武水別神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takemizuwake Shrine|qq=}}, a {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|qq=}} mentioned in Volumes 9 and 10 of the {{ill|Engishiki|ja|延喜式|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki|qq=}}. This shrine is located in the former {{ill|Sarashina District, Nagano|lt=Sarashina District|ja|更級郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sarashina District, Nagano|qq=}}, {{ill|Shinano Province|ja|信濃国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinano Province|qq=}}.
== Shrines == * {{ill|Takemizuwake Shrine|ja|武水別神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takemizuwake Shrine|qq=}} ({{ill|Chikuma, Nagano|ja|千曲市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chikuma, Nagano|qq=}}, Nagano Prefecture) * {{ill|Hijiri Shrine|ja|樋知大神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hijiri Shrine|qq=}} ({{ill|Nagano, Nagano|ja|長野市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagano, Nagano|qq=}}, Nagano Prefecture)
