'''Takeminawake no Mikoto''' (武美名別命) is a figure from ancient Japan.
== Overview == Takeminawake no Mikoto is considered the same deity as '''Takemizuwake Ōkami''' (武水別大神), worshipped at {{ill|Takemizuwake Shrine|ja|武水別神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takemizuwake Shrine|qq=}}, a {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|qq=}} mentioned in Volumes 9 and 10 of the [[:en:Engishiki|Engishiki]]. This shrine is located in the former [[:en:Sarashina District, Nagano|Sarashina District]], [[:en:Shinano Province|Shinano Province]].
== Shrines == * {{ill|Takemizuwake Shrine|ja|武水別神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takemizuwake Shrine|qq=}} ([[:en:Chikuma, Nagano|Chikuma, Nagano]], Nagano Prefecture) * {{ill|Hijiri Shrine|ja|樋知大神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hijiri Shrine|qq=}} ([[:en:Nagano (city)|Nagano, Nagano]], Nagano Prefecture)
